Now that we have the induction principle `existsOf_induction`, we can use it to prove the main goal of the lemma. The hypothesis `s_in` states that `s` is an exit from `exitsOf (tab.flip)`. By applying `existsOf_induction` to `s_in`, we get that `s.flip` is an exit from `exitsOf (tab.flip).flip`, which is `exitsOf tab`.

