**Step 2: Define the induction principle for `exitsOf`.**
The first part of our new proof is to establish an induction principle for `exitsOf`. This principle will state that for any path `p` in a `Tableau` `t`, if `p` is an exit, then `p.flip` is also an exit. This is captured by the induction principle `existsOf_induction`.

```tactics
  have existsOf_induction : ∀ t p, p ∈ exitsOf t → p.flip ∈ exitsOf t.flip := by
    intro t p hp
    inductionOn hp with
    | nil =>
      simp only [List.mem_nil, iff_false, Decidable.not_not]
      intro p hp
      simp only [List.mem_nil, iff_false, Decidable.not_not] at hp
      exfalso
      exact hp (by simp)
    | cons x xs ih =>
      simp only [List.mem_cons, List.mem_singleton]
      intro p hp
      rcases hp with (hp | hp)
      · simp only [List.mem_singleton] at hp
        rw [hp]
        exact ih rfl
      · simp only [List.mem_cons] at hp
        rcases hp with (hp | hp)
        · exact ih hp
        · exact ih hp
```

**Step 3: Use the induction principle to prove the main goal.**
Now that we have the induction principle `existsOf_induction`, we can use it to prove the main goal of the lemma. The hypothesis `s_in` states that `s` is an exit from `exitsOf (tab.flip)`. By applying `existsOf_induction` to `s_in`, we get that `s.flip` is an exit from `exitsOf (tab.flip).flip`, which is `exitsOf tab`.

```tactics
  apply existsOf_induction
  exact s_in
```

**Step 4: Finalize the proof structure.**
The combination of the induction principle and its application gives us a complete proof. The full proof block now looks like this:

```tactics
lemma mem_existsOf_of_flip {Hist L R lr_nlf} {tab : Tableau Hist (L, R, some lr_nlf)}
    (s : PathIn tab.flip) (s_in : s ∈ (exitsOf tab.flip : List (PathIn tab.flip)))
    : (PathIn_type_flip_flip ▸ s.flip) ∈ exitsOf tab := by
  have existsOf_induction : ∀ t p, p ∈ exitsOf t → p.flip ∈ exitsOf t.flip := by
    intro t p hp
    inductionOn hp with
    | nil =>
      simp only [List.mem_nil, iff_false, Decidable.not_not]
      intro p hp
      simp only [List.mem_nil, iff_false, Decidable.not_not] at hp
      exfalso
      exact hp (by simp)
    | cons x xs ih =>
      simp only [List.mem_cons, List.mem_singleton]
      intro p hp
      rcases hp with (hp | hp)
      · simp only [List.mem_singleton] at hp
        rw [hp]
        exact ih rfl
      · simp only [List.mem_cons] at hp
        rcases hp with (hp | hp)
        · exact ih hp
        · exact ih hp
  apply existsOf_induction
  exact s_in
```
